        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-06T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-06T11:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Sturgeon, Leo D.: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-06T11:00:00-05:00">March 6, 1946—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>400. Please get in touch immediately with appropriate Russian authorities and
                    request prompt action on the following matter:</p>
                <p>US Consul General, Leo D. Sturgeon, with staff, will leave Shanghai for Dairen on
                    or about March 6 aboard the SS <hi rend="italic">Check Knot. Check Knot</hi> is
                    expected to arrive Dairen on or about March 9. It is urgent that port
                    authorities at Dairen be advised to make arrangements to receive and berth the
                        <hi rend="italic">Check Knot</hi> on arrival at Dairen.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
